%text \textbf{Modulus } The modulus function is defined as follows % \[ \quad \vert x \vert = \begin{cases}
-x, &\text{ if }x < 0 \\ x, &\text{ if } x \geq 0 \end{cases} \] %text Note that $\vert x \vert$ is always $\geq 0$, even for $x < 0$ \textbf{Floor / Greatest Integer Function} Returns the largest integer $\leq x$. Also written as $[x]$, it is however recommended that one use the modern notation $\lfloor x \rfloor$ \textbf{Ceiling } Returns the smallest integer $\geq x$ The following table shows values for various $x$ for the above functions % \begin{align} \begin{tabular}{NNNN}
\hline x & \vert x \vert & \lfloor x\rfloor & \lceil x \rceil \\ \hline -1 & 1 & -1 & -1 \\ \hline -1.5 & 1.5 & -2 & -1 \\ \hline 2 & 2 & 2 & 2 \\ \hline 4.3 & 4.3 & 4 & 5 \\ \hline \end{tabular} \end{align} %text %
